ðŸ“˜ 1. Learning Path for SQL Date & String Functions
ðŸ”¹ Step 1: Basics

Learn how to extract and format values.

YEAR(date), MONTH(date), DAY(date)

DATEPART(), DATENAME()

LEN(), UPPER(), LOWER(), LTRIM(), RTRIM(), SUBSTRING()

ðŸ‘‰ Example:

SELECT YEAR('2020-06-15') AS year, 
       MONTH('2020-06-15') AS month,
       LEN('   hello  ') AS length,
       LTRIM('   hello  ') AS left_trimmed;

ðŸ”¹ Step 2: Intermediate

Learn arithmetic and manipulation

DATEADD(), DATEDIFF(), EOMONTH()

REPLACE(), CHARINDEX(), LEFT(), RIGHT()

ðŸ‘‰ Example:

SELECT DATEADD(DAY, 7, '2020-06-15') AS plus_7_days,
       DATEDIFF(DAY, '2020-06-01', '2020-06-15') AS days_between,
       REPLACE('SQL IS FUN', 'FUN', 'POWERFUL') AS replaced;

ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Advanced

Work with formatting & conversion

FORMAT(), CONVERT(), CAST()

STUFF(), PATINDEX()

Time-zone aware: SYSDATETIMEOFFSET(), SWITCHOFFSET()

ðŸ‘‰ Example:

SELECT FORMAT(GETDATE(), 'yyyy-MM-dd') AS formatted_date,
       STUFF('123456', 2, 3, 'XYZ') AS stuffed;
